{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Negro employees brought a class action against employer on ground that employment practices violated the Civil Rights Act. The District Court, Gordon, J., held that evidence established that high school education requirement of employer did not as to Negro employees violate provision of Civil Rights Act that it shall be unlawful employment practice for employer to discriminate against any individual with respect to compensation, terms, conditions, or privileges of employment, because of race, color, religion, sex, or national origin.
\par 
}
}
}
