 dismissed complaint and plaintiffs appealed. The Court of Appeals, Boreman, Circuit Judge, held that six Negro employees without high school education or its equivalent who were hired prior to adoption of requirement of high school education for promotion were entitled to injunctive relief, but Negro employees hired after adoption of requirement were not entitled to relief.
\par 
}
}
