1. That defendant, Duke Power Company, its officers, agents, employees, servants, successors and all persons and organizations in active concert or participation with them are hereby Enjoined and Restrained from discriminating against plaintiffs, Junior Blackstock, William Purcell, Clarence Jackson, Eddie Galloway, Lewis Hairston, and James Tucker, at the defendant\rquote s Dan River Steam Station, located in Draper, North Carolina, because of their race in violation of Title VII of the Civil Rights Act of 1964, 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000546&cite=42USCAS2000E&originatingDoc=I62820770550011d9bf30d7fdf51b6bd4&refType=LQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.UserEnteredCitation)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
