{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
. Plaintiffs, however, continue to contend that for purposes of injunctive relief they represent a class of all black persons who may be employed subsequent to October 20, 1966 (the date this action was initiated). For all practical purposes, it is clear that this suit is no longer, if it ever was, a class action. Therefore, it is concluded that this Court\rquote s Order of June 19, 1967, permitting this suit to be brought as a class action, was implicitly dissolved by the decision of the Court of Appeals.
