{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs18 \sa200 \sb0 
This does not mean that the Court disbelieves the testimony of the plaintiffs. On the contrary, it is quite likely that the plaintiffs who refused the job did genuinely believe that the offer was a bad faith attempt to eliminate their employment. However, the Court cannot infer such an intention by the defendant as a fact. Fear and distrust are unfortunate products of any labor dispute, but they are beyond the power of any court to remedy. After five years of litigation and widespread publicity it is only natural for the plaintiffs to be skeptical of all actions by the defendant which affect them.
\par 
}
}
