{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
2. The class of persons entitled to relief under this Order, referred to hereinafter as the \u8220\'3faffected class,\u8221\'3f is designated and described as:
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Group I
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u8211\'3fAll black persons employed at the defendant\rquote s Dan River Steam Station as of October 20, 1966 (date this action was initiated); and
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Group II
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u8211\'3fAll black persons who may subsequently be employed at defendant\rquote s Dan River Steam Station.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
See Order on class, June 19, 1967.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
3. The defendant Duke Power Company is hereby Permanently Enjoined and Restrained from requiring any Group I members of the affected class to meet or satisfy the education and test requirements in effect prior to March 8, 1971, in considering the selection of employees for promotions, transfers, demotions or lay-offs and the selection of employees for training for any of the job vacancies which may hereafter occur at the defendant\rquote s Dan River Steam Station.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_anchor_I15c2f8a189db11e598dc8b09b4f04}{\*\bkmkend co_anchor_I15c2f8a189db11e598dc8b09b4f04}
\par 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
[
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Test or Diploma Requirement Barred
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa200 \sb400 
]
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
4. The defendant Duke Power Company is hereby Permanently Enjoined and Restrained from administering any personnel or aptitude tests or requiring any formal educational background which the defendant had in effect prior to March 8, 1971, as a condition of consideration for employment or promotion or transfer at its Dan River Steam Station for Group II members of the affected class.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_anchor_I15c2f8a289db11e598dc8b09b4f04}{\*\bkmkend co_anchor_I15c2f8a289db11e598dc8b09b4f04}
\par 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
[
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Job Related Test Permitted
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa200 \sb400 
]
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
5. This Order does not prevent the defendant from applying and acting upon the results of reasonable ability demonstrations for members of the affected class with respect to actual job content, such as the demonstration of driving ability by prospective truck drivers, provided, however, that any such demonstrations are fairly related to the requirements of the particular job in question and are reasonable in terms of the weight accorded to the results of these demonstrations in terms of overall employment decisions.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_anchor_I15c2f8a389db11e598dc8b09b4f04}{\*\bkmkend co_anchor_I15c2f8a389db11e598dc8b09b4f04}
\par 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
[
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Seniority Provisions
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa200 \sb400 
]
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
6. The defendant Duke Power Company is hereby Permanently Enjoined and Restrained from using any seniority provisions in effect prior to and subsequent to July 2, 1965, which is designed or tends to discriminate against members of the affected class, or has the effect of discriminating against members of the affected class because of their race. The defendant is Ordered to offer members of the affected class the opportunity to qualify for promotions and transfers to vacancies on the basis of total plant seniority (i.e., the length of continuous service).
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 The defendant shall consider members of the affected class on the basis of plant seniority as demotions and lay-offs occur.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 
}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\*\bkmkstart co_pp_sp_999_2_11}{\*\bkmkend co_pp_sp_999_2_11}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
*2
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 7. Should any member of the affected class qualify for a promotion or transfer to any vacancy which hereafter may occur based on his plant seniority and is not offered the opportunity to otherwise qualify for the promotion or transfer, the defendant is directed to state the reasons for such disqualification in writing, to place a copy in the employment personnel folder and to send or give each such employee a copy.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_anchor_I15c2f8a489db11e598dc8b09b4f04}{\*\bkmkend co_anchor_I15c2f8a489db11e598dc8b09b4f04}
\par 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
[
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Terms of Job Transfers
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa200 \sb400 
]
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
8. Defendant shall institute a system of \u8220\'3frate retention\u8221\'3f whereby any member of Group I of the affected class who is promoted to or is transferred to a job which carries a lower wage rate than he is currently paid shall continue to receive the rate of pay he was receiving on the job prior to his transfer or promotion until he is permanently assigned to a position paying an equivalent or higher rate of pay.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
9. Members of Group I of the affected class shall be allowed to by-pass all jobs, including entry level jobs, in any department or promotion or transfer where such jobs do not provide training or experience necessary to the performance of higher positions in the department.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
10. The defendant shall post written notice of all permanent vacancies and temporary vacancies expected to last two weeks or more in conspicuous places at its Dan River Steam Station in a manner which is reasonably designed to be called to the attention of members of the affected class in order that members of the affected class may have the opportunity to bid and qualify for such vacancies.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
11. The defendant shall maintain appropriate records of all personnel assignments and action made at its Dan River Steam Station, and the defendant shall allow reasonable inspection of these records by counsel for the plaintiffs at reasonable times and after fifteen days written notice.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
12. The defendant shall post for a period of thirty days a copy of this Judgment in some conspicuous place at its Dan River Steam Station.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
13. The costs incurred in this proceeding are taxed against the defendant Duke Power Company. As part of the costs, plaintiffs are entitled to reasonable counsel fees. If after twenty days the parties have not been able to agree upon a fee, the Court will allow it upon consideration of a statement of services filed and served upon counsel for the defendant, who will have ten days to serve and file a response.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
14. The Court will retain jurisdiction of this matter to issue such other Orders and to conduct such proceedings as may be necessary to effectuate this Order.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
}
}
}
}
}
